narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This was a good and relatively easy introduction to the topic.
Good class to pretty rigorously get a foundation in Plato and Aristotle.

This is an excellent class, and Matt Evans is an excellent professor. The presocratics are a little crazy, but they are worth studying because they help you understand Plato and Aristotle. Basically, the class proceeds as follows: the professor writes down the premises and conclusion of a a few arguments, and then everyone criticizes the arguments. If you have a section a**whole, then this could be a problem, but everyone in our class was pretty respectful, and it made for some of the greatest class discussions I had at Yale. Basically, if you believe that this material is important, you'll love the class, but if you think Metaphysics might just all be sophistry, you might find this incredibly boring.
